# Authentication

## JWT (`auth.service.js`)

- Payload: `{ id, email, role }`; secret `JWT_SECRET`; expiry `1h`
- Delivery: httpOnly cookie `token` (`#utils/cookies.js`, 15 min) or `Authorization: Bearer <token>`

## Middleware (`auth.middleware.js`)

- **`authenticateToken`** → `req.user = { id, email, role }`; 401 if missing/invalid
- **`requireRole(...roles)`** → 403 if role not allowed

Never parse JWT in controllers; use `req.user` only.

## Auth routes `/api/auth`

| Method | Path | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| POST | `/signup` | `signupSchema`, `createUser`, cookie + token |
| POST | `/signin` | `signinSchema`, `authenticateUser`; 401 `Invalid email or password` |
| POST | `/signout` | `cookies.clear(res, 'token')` |

- Signin: `USER_NOT_FOUND` / `INVALID_PASSWORD` → 401 (generic message)
- Signup duplicate → 409 via `isEmailAlreadyExistsError`

## User routes `/api/users`

All routes: `usersRoutes.use(authenticateToken)`.

| Method | Path | Extra | Rules |
|--------|------|-------|-------|
| GET | `/` | — | List users (no passwords) |
| GET | `/:id` | — | `userIdSchema` on params |
| PUT | `/:id` | — | Non-admin: own id only; `role` admin-only |
| DELETE | `/:id` | `requireRole('admin')` | Admin only |

**`updateUser` controller:** strip `role` for non-admins; 403 if non-admin sends `role`.

## User service (`users.services.js`)

- `publicUserColumns` — never expose `password`
- `getUserById` → row or `null`
- `updateUser` → `USER_NOT_FOUND`, email uniqueness, `hashPassword`, `updated_at`
- `deleteUser` → `USER_NOT_FOUND` if missing

## Zod (`users.validation.js`)

- `userIdSchema`: `z.coerce.number().int().positive()`
- `updateUserSchema`: optional `name`, `email`, `password`, `role`; min one field
